Prolog CLP Programs
by Jimmy Nguyen (Jimmy@Jimmyworks.net)

Introduction

The files in this repository were generated while learning Prolog 
and include the following Prolog CLP programs:

1 - Crypt-Arithmetic Puzzle Solver
2 - Sudoku Puzzle Generator and Solver

Required Steps

1. You will need a load these programs using a Prolog environment. If
you do not have a Prolog environment installed, you can download and
install it here:  http://www.swi-prolog.org/Download.html

2. Clone this repository to your local machine.
3. Run Prolog interactive environment.
4. Consult the appropriate .pl file.  This can be done with File > Consult...
5. Execute Prolog statements.
